The error **"The AI Server is currently busy/overloaded"** (Error 503) means that Google's **Nano Banana Pro** model is currently experiencing high traffic and cannot process the request immediately. This is common with "Preview" models.

However, on Vercel's free tier, serverless functions have a **10-second timeout**. My previous code included a "Retry" mechanism (waiting 2s, then 4s) which, when added to the generation time, often causes the Vercel function to time out before it can even tell you the result.

I will **optimize the backend** to remove the internal wait loop. This ensures the request fails fast if Google is busy, preventing the browser from hanging, and allows you to just click "Retry" immediately. I will also ensure the **2K resolution** is set as default.

